The second season of Hataraku Maou-sama! Sadao Maou returns for more shifts, now having to take care of a small girl born from a golden apple! (Source: Crunchyroll)

The third season of Log Horizon. It’s been a year since Shiroe and his friends were trapped in Akiba due to the Catastrophe. Their forging of the Round Table has brought order and prosperity to its people. But fracturing political alliances and the constant menace of the Genius monsters threaten to destabilize all they’ve fought for and built. Can faith be restored and they persevere, or is its destruction truly inevitable? (Source: Funimation)

Oscar is a prince cursed to never sire an heir. He seeks out Tinasha, a witch who grants the wish of any who manages to climb her tower. But when he arrives at the top…he requests that Tinasha become his bride! (Source: Yen Press)
Kaoru Hana wa Rin to Saku

In a certain place, there were two neighboring high schools: Chidori High School, a bottom-feeder boys' school full of delinquents, and Kikyo Girls' School, a fancy girls' private school. Rintaro Tsumugi, a strong and quiet second year student at Chidori High, meets Kaoruko Wakuri, a girl who visited his family's cake shop while he was helping out. Rintaro feels comfortable spending time with Kaoruko. However, she is a student at Kikyo, and all of the girls there seems to hate Chidori boys.
This is the story of two people who are so close and yet so far apart.
